pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- Created base structure for Guided Tour.
- This feature is a click-through path which the user can follow to fulfill certain tasks and it will increase the convenience for the users.
- With this feature users don't need to read the bulky documentation.

### Testing Instructions

- Apply the patch.
- Go to System and click on Plugin under the Manage section.
- Enable the `Guided Tours` plugin.
- Click on `Guided Tours` under the Manage section.
- Now, as the Plugin is enabled you can see the `Take the Tour` button.
- Click on the `Take the Tour` button and select the Guided Tour which you want.

![Guided Tour](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316197-39c8e30a-3928-4be0-a5dc-6f9d0b321475.PNG)

![Guided Tour 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316213-ec0d658a-8de3-404f-824c-12f9c1542b63.PNG)

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

- Guided Tour functionality was not present.

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

- Included Guided Tour functionality.

### Summary

- [x] Created Base Structure for Guided Tour.
- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Created Relative URL for Steps and Tours.
- [x] Removed the `https://` from the URL to make the tour work.
- [x] Solved URL problem for Tours Page. 
- [x] Made `Back Button` Functional for Multi-Page.
- [x] Added String Value for Archived Tours.
- [x] Added Table Structure and data for Guided Tours and Steps for Postgresql.
- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Changes done in PR: https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/10.
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.
- [x] Added form fields in the tour step for an interactive tour.
- [x] Changed value for interactive step field in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Add a new dropdown field that would be visible after selecting Interactive tour which has two options - Button and Text Field.
- [x] Solved the major problem for the interactive step and made `+New Button` Working.
- [x]  If the user selects the `Button` field then the user will be able to click the `+New button` in spite of clicking on the `Next Button` in the pop-up.
- [x] On selecting the `Button` field the Next Button won't be visible.
- [x] If the user selects the `Text field` then it will disable the Next Button until someone enters any value in the field.
- [x] Added EventListner `Click` on the target of the step for the Button field in Interactive Tour.
- [x] Added EventListner `input` on the target of the step for Form Field.
- [x] Done changes for default tours in `extensions.sql` for changing the value according to Interactive tour.
- [x] Code formatting.
- [x] Added one more field in the `Interactive step` for default values.
- [x] Added logic in javascript for incorporating changes for adding one more field in the `Interactive step`.
- [x] Made changes in default tours in `extensions.sql`  to make it compatible with interactive tours.
- [x] Identified and solved the problem and made two consecutive mandatory fields `Next Button` enable/disable in the `interactive step` work.
- [x] Tested the changes done for all the default tours to ensure all the tours are working with interaction.
- [x] Did the changes in Default tours and made improvements in interactive tours.
- [x] Done Update SQL scripts fixes for MySQL and PostgreSQL.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour` Table : language column, note column, index state, index language.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour-steps`  Table : language column, note column, index state, index language, modified column `setp-no` to `step_no`, modified column `interactivetour` to `interactive_type`.
- [x] Addition of an admin module in replacement to the toolbars.
- [x] Calls via Ajax to avoid refreshes if the module is on the same page of a tour.
- [x] Changed `Step Name` to `Step`.
- [x] Changed `Interactive Tour` to `Interactive Step` in Steps.
- [x] Added Step Type column in Steps.
- [x] Fixed PHP 8.1 depreciation error.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Tours.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Steps.
- [x] Admin module database changes.
- [x] Tours in the database have been replaced with language keys for proper translations.
- [x] Empty state for steps view when no step has ever been created for a tour.
- [x] Added getEmptyStateQuery to return the steps of a tour.
- [x] Added columns access, featured, and locked.
- [x] Replaced 'click' with `select` in steps.
- [x] Fix EOF.
- [x] Fix filter forms (default sort, dropdown elements ordering).
- [x] Component name lowercase in the manifest.
- [x] Cleanup component provider.
- [x] Converted module `mod_guidedtour`s to services.
- [x] Remove loading of language files.
- [x] Fixed the `Take a Tour` button visible before logging in.
- [x] Added focus on targeted elements.
- [x] Changes to tours to render targeted elements.
- [x] Accessible (in some cases, targeted elements were not tab-able).
- [x] Tours can't show if no user is logged in.
- [x] Selection of tours per language, access and component authorization.
- [x] Fixed Step Permission.
- [x] Reordering of the steps according to `tour_id`.
- [x] Created Empty State for Tours.
- [x] Languages inherited from parent tour in steps.
- [x] Added access column in tours.
- [x] Added note section for tours and steps.
- [x] Core tours and their steps, in a multilingual environment, can not be saved or else language keys are overridden.
- [x] Formatted database queries.
- [x] Created functionality for tour duplication along with its steps.
- [x] The step count only considers the number of published steps.
- [x] Fixed the width of the step table.
- [x] Unsets the `tour_id `from the active filters so that the search tools open in a closed state.
- [x] Allowed the creation of a custom admin menu for the guided tours component.
- [x] Fixed Typos in order url task attribute.
- [x] Fixed saving to asset table.
- [x] Removed the step_no column.
- [x] Ordering in the script, done through ordering property and not id.
- [x] Fixes for saving tours and steps.
- [x] Added a Full list of buttons to remove in editor `hide`.
- [x] Fixed `bleeding` over popup. 
- [x] Added empty state.


#### Added default Tours that need to be created, to be packaged with Joomla Basic tours required for this project.

- [x] Guided Tour Introduction
- [x] Content > Articles
- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

Fixing the issue and code clean-up in the Base Guided Tour.

- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.

pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- Created base structure for Guided Tour.
- This feature is a click-through path which the user can follow to fulfill certain tasks and it will increase the convenience for the users.
- With this feature users don't need to read the bulky documentation.

### Testing Instructions

- Apply the patch.
- Go to System and click on Plugin under the Manage section.
- Enable the `Guided Tours` plugin.
- Click on `Guided Tours` under the Manage section.
- Now, as the Plugin is enabled you can see the `Take the Tour` button.
- Click on the `Take the Tour` button and select the Guided Tour which you want.

![Guided Tour](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316197-39c8e30a-3928-4be0-a5dc-6f9d0b321475.PNG)

![Guided Tour 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316213-ec0d658a-8de3-404f-824c-12f9c1542b63.PNG)

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

- Guided Tour functionality was not present.

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

- Included Guided Tour functionality.

### Summary

- [x] Created Base Structure for Guided Tour.
- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Created Relative URL for Steps and Tours.
- [x] Removed the `https://` from the URL to make the tour work.
- [x] Solved URL problem for Tours Page. 
- [x] Made `Back Button` Functional for Multi-Page.
- [x] Added String Value for Archived Tours.
- [x] Added Table Structure and data for Guided Tours and Steps for Postgresql.
- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Changes done in PR: https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/10.
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.
- [x] Added form fields in the tour step for an interactive tour.
- [x] Changed value for interactive step field in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Add a new dropdown field that would be visible after selecting Interactive tour which has two options - Button and Text Field.
- [x] Solved the major problem for the interactive step and made `+New Button` Working.
- [x]  If the user selects the `Button` field then the user will be able to click the `+New button` in spite of clicking on the `Next Button` in the pop-up.
- [x] On selecting the `Button` field the Next Button won't be visible.
- [x] If the user selects the `Text field` then it will disable the Next Button until someone enters any value in the field.
- [x] Added EventListner `Click` on the target of the step for the Button field in Interactive Tour.
- [x] Added EventListner `input` on the target of the step for Form Field.
- [x] Done changes for default tours in `extensions.sql` for changing the value according to Interactive tour.
- [x] Code formatting.
- [x] Added one more field in the `Interactive step` for default values.
- [x] Added logic in javascript for incorporating changes for adding one more field in the `Interactive step`.
- [x] Made changes in default tours in `extensions.sql`  to make it compatible with interactive tours.
- [x] Identified and solved the problem and made two consecutive mandatory fields `Next Button` enable/disable in the `interactive step` work.
- [x] Tested the changes done for all the default tours to ensure all the tours are working with interaction.
- [x] Did the changes in Default tours and made improvements in interactive tours.
- [x] Done Update SQL scripts fixes for MySQL and PostgreSQL.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour` Table : language column, note column, index state, index language.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour-steps`  Table : language column, note column, index state, index language, modified column `setp-no` to `step_no`, modified column `interactivetour` to `interactive_type`.
- [x] Addition of an admin module in replacement to the toolbars.
- [x] Calls via Ajax to avoid refreshes if the module is on the same page of a tour.
- [x] Changed `Step Name` to `Step`.
- [x] Changed `Interactive Tour` to `Interactive Step` in Steps.
- [x] Added Step Type column in Steps.
- [x] Fixed PHP 8.1 depreciation error.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Tours.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Steps.
- [x] Admin module database changes.
- [x] Tours in the database have been replaced with language keys for proper translations.
- [x] Empty state for steps view when no step has ever been created for a tour.
- [x] Added getEmptyStateQuery to return the steps of a tour.
- [x] Added columns access, featured, and locked.
- [x] Replaced 'click' with `select` in steps.
- [x] Fix EOF.
- [x] Fix filter forms (default sort, dropdown elements ordering).
- [x] Component name lowercase in the manifest.
- [x] Cleanup component provider.
- [x] Converted module `mod_guidedtour`s to services.
- [x] Remove loading of language files.
- [x] Fixed the `Take a Tour` button visible before logging in.
- [x] Added focus on targeted elements.
- [x] Changes to tours to render targeted elements.
- [x] Accessible (in some cases, targeted elements were not tab-able).
- [x] Tours can't show if no user is logged in.
- [x] Selection of tours per language, access and component authorization.
- [x] Fixed Step Permission.
- [x] Reordering of the steps according to `tour_id`.
- [x] Created Empty State for Tours.
- [x] Languages inherited from parent tour in steps.
- [x] Added access column in tours.
- [x] Added note section for tours and steps.
- [x] Core tours and their steps, in a multilingual environment, can not be saved or else language keys are overridden.
- [x] Formatted database queries.
- [x] Created functionality for tour duplication along with its steps.
- [x] The step count only considers the number of published steps.
- [x] Fixed the width of the step table.
- [x] Unsets the `tour_id `from the active filters so that the search tools open in a closed state.
- [x] Allowed the creation of a custom admin menu for the guided tours component.
- [x] Fixed Typos in order url task attribute.
- [x] Fixed saving to asset table.
- [x] Removed the step_no column.
- [x] Ordering in the script, done through ordering property and not id.
- [x] Fixes for saving tours and steps.
- [x] Added a Full list of buttons to remove in editor `hide`.
- [x] Fixed `bleeding` over popup. 
- [x] Added empty state.


#### Added default Tours that need to be created, to be packaged with Joomla Basic tours required for this project.

- [x] Guided Tour Introduction
- [x] Content > Articles
- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- Created base structure for Guided Tour.
- This feature is a click-through path which the user can follow to fulfill certain tasks and it will increase the convenience for the users.
- With this feature users don't need to read the bulky documentation.

### Testing Instructions

- Apply the patch.
- Go to System and click on Plugin under the Manage section.
- Enable the `Guided Tours` plugin.
- Click on `Guided Tours` under the Manage section.
- Now, as the Plugin is enabled you can see the `Take the Tour` button.
- Click on the `Take the Tour` button and select the Guided Tour which you want.

![Guided Tour](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316197-39c8e30a-3928-4be0-a5dc-6f9d0b321475.PNG)

![Guided Tour 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316213-ec0d658a-8de3-404f-824c-12f9c1542b63.PNG)

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

- Guided Tour functionality was not present.

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

- Included Guided Tour functionality.

### Summary

- [x] Created Base Structure for Guided Tour.
- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Created Relative URL for Steps and Tours.
- [x] Removed the `https://` from the URL to make the tour work.
- [x] Solved URL problem for Tours Page. 
- [x] Made `Back Button` Functional for Multi-Page.
- [x] Added String Value for Archived Tours.
- [x] Added Table Structure and data for Guided Tours and Steps for Postgresql.
- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Changes done in PR: https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/10.
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.
- [x] Added form fields in the tour step for an interactive tour.
- [x] Changed value for interactive step field in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Add a new dropdown field that would be visible after selecting Interactive tour which has two options - Button and Text Field.
- [x] Solved the major problem for the interactive step and made `+New Button` Working.
- [x]  If the user selects the `Button` field then the user will be able to click the `+New button` in spite of clicking on the `Next Button` in the pop-up.
- [x] On selecting the `Button` field the Next Button won't be visible.
- [x] If the user selects the `Text field` then it will disable the Next Button until someone enters any value in the field.
- [x] Added EventListner `Click` on the target of the step for the Button field in Interactive Tour.
- [x] Added EventListner `input` on the target of the step for Form Field.
- [x] Done changes for default tours in `extensions.sql` for changing the value according to Interactive tour.
- [x] Code formatting.
- [x] Added one more field in the `Interactive step` for default values.
- [x] Added logic in javascript for incorporating changes for adding one more field in the `Interactive step`.
- [x] Made changes in default tours in `extensions.sql`  to make it compatible with interactive tours.
- [x] Identified and solved the problem and made two consecutive mandatory fields `Next Button` enable/disable in the `interactive step` work.
- [x] Tested the changes done for all the default tours to ensure all the tours are working with interaction.
- [x] Did the changes in Default tours and made improvements in interactive tours.
- [x] Done Update SQL scripts fixes for MySQL and PostgreSQL.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour` Table : language column, note column, index state, index language.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour-steps`  Table : language column, note column, index state, index language, modified column `setp-no` to `step_no`, modified column `interactivetour` to `interactive_type`.
- [x] Addition of an admin module in replacement to the toolbars.
- [x] Calls via Ajax to avoid refreshes if the module is on the same page of a tour.
- [x] Changed `Step Name` to `Step`.
- [x] Changed `Interactive Tour` to `Interactive Step` in Steps.
- [x] Added Step Type column in Steps.
- [x] Fixed PHP 8.1 depreciation error.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Tours.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Steps.
- [x] Admin module database changes.
- [x] Tours in the database have been replaced with language keys for proper translations.
- [x] Empty state for steps view when no step has ever been created for a tour.
- [x] Added getEmptyStateQuery to return the steps of a tour.
- [x] Added columns access, featured, and locked.
- [x] Replaced 'click' with `select` in steps.
- [x] Fix EOF.
- [x] Fix filter forms (default sort, dropdown elements ordering).
- [x] Component name lowercase in the manifest.
- [x] Cleanup component provider.
- [x] Converted module `mod_guidedtour`s to services.
- [x] Remove loading of language files.
- [x] Fixed the `Take a Tour` button visible before logging in.
- [x] Added focus on targeted elements.
- [x] Changes to tours to render targeted elements.
- [x] Accessible (in some cases, targeted elements were not tab-able).
- [x] Tours can't show if no user is logged in.
- [x] Selection of tours per language, access and component authorization.
- [x] Fixed Step Permission.
- [x] Reordering of the steps according to `tour_id`.
- [x] Created Empty State for Tours.
- [x] Languages inherited from parent tour in steps.
- [x] Added access column in tours.
- [x] Added note section for tours and steps.
- [x] Core tours and their steps, in a multilingual environment, can not be saved or else language keys are overridden.
- [x] Formatted database queries.
- [x] Created functionality for tour duplication along with its steps.
- [x] The step count only considers the number of published steps.
- [x] Fixed the width of the step table.
- [x] Unsets the `tour_id `from the active filters so that the search tools open in a closed state.
- [x] Allowed the creation of a custom admin menu for the guided tours component.
- [x] Fixed Typos in order url task attribute.
- [x] Fixed saving to asset table.
- [x] Removed the step_no column.
- [x] Ordering in the script, done through ordering property and not id.
- [x] Fixes for saving tours and steps.
- [x] Added a Full list of buttons to remove in editor `hide`.
- [x] Fixed `bleeding` over popup. 
- [x] Added empty state.

- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- Created base structure for Guided Tour.
- This feature is a click-through path which the user can follow to fulfill certain tasks and it will increase the convenience for the users.
- With this feature users don't need to read the bulky documentation.

### Testing Instructions

- Apply the patch.
- Go to System and click on Plugin under the Manage section.
- Enable the `Guided Tours` plugin.
- Click on `Guided Tours` under the Manage section.
- Now, as the Plugin is enabled you can see the `Take the Tour` button.
- Click on the `Take the Tour` button and select the Guided Tour which you want.

![Guided Tour](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316197-39c8e30a-3928-4be0-a5dc-6f9d0b321475.PNG)

![Guided Tour 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316213-ec0d658a-8de3-404f-824c-12f9c1542b63.PNG)

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

- Guided Tour functionality was not present.

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

- Included Guided Tour functionality.

### Summary

- [x] Created Base Structure for Guided Tour.
- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Created Relative URL for Steps and Tours.
- [x] Removed the `https://` from the URL to make the tour work.
- [x] Solved URL problem for Tours Page. 
- [x] Made `Back Button` Functional for Multi-Page.
- [x] Added String Value for Archived Tours.
- [x] Added Table Structure and data for Guided Tours and Steps for Postgresql.
- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Changes done in PR: https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/10.
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.
- [x] Added form fields in the tour step for an interactive tour.
- [x] Changed value for interactive step field in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Add a new dropdown field that would be visible after selecting Interactive tour which has two options - Button and Text Field.
- [x] Solved the major problem for the interactive step and made `+New Button` Working.
- [x]  If the user selects the `Button` field then the user will be able to click the `+New button` in spite of clicking on the `Next Button` in the pop-up.
- [x] On selecting the `Button` field the Next Button won't be visible.
- [x] If the user selects the `Text field` then it will disable the Next Button until someone enters any value in the field.
- [x] Added EventListner `Click` on the target of the step for the Button field in Interactive Tour.
- [x] Added EventListner `input` on the target of the step for Form Field.
- [x] Done changes for default tours in `extensions.sql` for changing the value according to Interactive tour.
- [x] Code formatting.
- [x] Added one more field in the `Interactive step` for default values.
- [x] Added logic in javascript for incorporating changes for adding one more field in the `Interactive step`.
- [x] Made changes in default tours in `extensions.sql`  to make it compatible with interactive tours.
- [x] Identified and solved the problem and made two consecutive mandatory fields `Next Button` enable/disable in the `interactive step` work.
- [x] Tested the changes done for all the default tours to ensure all the tours are working with interaction.
- [x] Did the changes in Default tours and made improvements in interactive tours.
- [x] Done Update SQL scripts fixes for MySQL and PostgreSQL.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour` Table : language column, note column, index state, index language.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour-steps`  Table : language column, note column, index state, index language, modified column `setp-no` to `step_no`, modified column `interactivetour` to `interactive_type`.
- [x] Addition of an admin module in replacement to the toolbars.
- [x] Calls via Ajax to avoid refreshes if the module is on the same page of a tour.
- [x] Changed `Step Name` to `Step`.
- [x] Changed `Interactive Tour` to `Interactive Step` in Steps.
- [x] Added Step Type column in Steps.
- [x] Fixed PHP 8.1 depreciation error.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Tours.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Steps.
- [x] Admin module database changes.
- [x] Tours in the database have been replaced with language keys for proper translations.
- [x] Empty state for steps view when no step has ever been created for a tour.
- [x] Added getEmptyStateQuery to return the steps of a tour.
- [x] Added columns access, featured, and locked.
- [x] Replaced 'click' with `select` in steps.
- [x] Fix EOF.
- [x] Fix filter forms (default sort, dropdown elements ordering).
- [x] Component name lowercase in the manifest.
- [x] Cleanup component provider.
- [x] Converted module `mod_guidedtour`s to services.
- [x] Remove loading of language files.
- [x] Fixed the `Take a Tour` button visible before logging in.
- [x] Added focus on targeted elements.
- [x] Changes to tours to render targeted elements.
- [x] Accessible (in some cases, targeted elements were not tab-able).
- [x] Tours can't show if no user is logged in.
- [x] Selection of tours per language, access and component authorization.
- [x] Fixed Step Permission.
- [x] Reordering of the steps according to `tour_id`.
- [x] Created Empty State for Tours.
- [x] Languages inherited from parent tour in steps.
- [x] Added access column in tours.
- [x] Added note section for tours and steps.
- [x] Core tours and their steps, in a multilingual environment, can not be saved or else language keys are overridden.
- [x] Formatted database queries.
- [x] Created functionality for tour duplication along with its steps.
- [x] The step count only considers the number of published steps.
- [x] Fixed the width of the step table.
- [x] Unsets the `tour_id `from the active filters so that the search tools open in a closed state.
- [x] Allowed the creation of a custom admin menu for the guided tours component.
- [x] Fixed Typos in order url task attribute.
- [x] Fixed saving to asset table.
- [x] Removed the step_no column.
- [x] Ordering in the script, done through ordering property and not id.
- [x] Fixes for saving tours and steps.
- [x] Added a Full list of buttons to remove in editor `hide`.
- [x] Fixed `bleeding` over popup. 
- [x] Added empty state.


#### Added default Tours that need to be created, to be packaged with Joomla Basic tours required for this project.

- [x] Guided Tour Introduction
- [x] Content > Articles
- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

pr_body:
Pull Request for PR #6 .

### Summary of Changes

This Pull Request (PR) fixes errors in the installation and update SQL scripts and one error in the tours model and adapts the update SQL scripts to the enhancements made with PR https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/37156 for the 4.2 version for more fault tolerant update SQL scripts.

The changes have been made with several commits in a comprehensive way so you can understand why a change has been made.

Simply go to the list of commits of this PR. You can expand the descriptions with details or links to details by using the "..." right beside the title of each commit.

By clicking on the title (or better right click and chose open in a new tab) you can then see the changes made with this commit.

### Testing Instructions

Check that a new installation and after that login to backend work without SQL errors on all kinds or supported databases (MySQL or MariaDB and PostgreSQL).

Check that updating any 3.10 or 4.x version to a package build with this PR and after that login to backend work without SQL errors on all kinds or supported databases (MySQL or MariaDB and PostgreSQL).

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

New installations and updates fail for sure with PostgreSQL.

Hard-coded user IDs used for created by and modified by users for the new data on new installations and updates.

On PostgreSQL you get an SQL error due to hardcoded MySQL names quotes being used in an SQL query in the guided tours model.

MySQL data types were used in SQL scripts for PostgreSQL.

Wrong data types (strings instead of numbers or datetimes/timestamps) used for values in insert statements.

....

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

No such errors anymore.

### Documentation Changes Required

None.

Pull Request for Issue #7.

### Summary of Changes
#### Added default Tours that need to be created, to be packaged with Joomla Basic tours required for this project.

- [x] Guided Tour Introduction
- [x] Content > Articles
- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

#### Other Changes
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.

- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.

- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- Created base structure for Guided Tour.
- This feature is a click-through path which the user can follow to fulfill certain tasks and it will increase the convenience for the users.
- With this feature users don't need to read the bulky documentation.

### Testing Instructions

- Apply the patch.
- Go to System and click on Plugin under the Manage section.
- Enable the `Guided Tours` plugin.
- Click on `Guided Tours` under the Manage section.
- Now, as the Plugin is enabled you can see the `Take the Tour` button.
- Click on the `Take the Tour` button and select the Guided Tour which you want.

![Guided Tour](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316197-39c8e30a-3928-4be0-a5dc-6f9d0b321475.PNG)

![Guided Tour 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316213-ec0d658a-8de3-404f-824c-12f9c1542b63.PNG)

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

- Guided Tour functionality was not present.

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

- Included Guided Tour functionality.

### Summary

- [x] Created Base Structure for Guided Tour.
- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Created Relative URL for Steps and Tours.
- [x] Removed the `https://` from the URL to make the tour work.
- [x] Solved URL problem for Tours Page. 
- [x] Made `Back Button` Functional for Multi-Page.
- [x] Added String Value for Archived Tours.
- [x] Added Table Structure and data for Guided Tours and Steps for Postgresql.
- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Changes done in PR: https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/10.
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.
- [x] Added form fields in the tour step for an interactive tour.
- [x] Changed value for interactive step field in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Add a new dropdown field that would be visible after selecting Interactive tour which has two options - Button and Text Field.
- [x] Solved the major problem for the interactive step and made `+New Button` Working.
- [x]  If the user selects the `Button` field then the user will be able to click the `+New button` in spite of clicking on the `Next Button` in the pop-up.
- [x] On selecting the `Button` field the Next Button won't be visible.
- [x] If the user selects the `Text field` then it will disable the Next Button until someone enters any value in the field.
- [x] Added EventListner `Click` on the target of the step for the Button field in Interactive Tour.
- [x] Added EventListner `input` on the target of the step for Form Field.
- [x] Done changes for default tours in `extensions.sql` for changing the value according to Interactive tour.
- [x] Code formatting.
- [x] Added one more field in the `Interactive step` for default values.
- [x] Added logic in javascript for incorporating changes for adding one more field in the `Interactive step`.
- [x] Made changes in default tours in `extensions.sql`  to make it compatible with interactive tours.
- [x] Identified and solved the problem and made two consecutive mandatory fields `Next Button` enable/disable in the `interactive step` work.
- [x] Tested the changes done for all the default tours to ensure all the tours are working with interaction.
- [x] Did the changes in Default tours and made improvements in interactive tours.
- [x] Done Update SQL scripts fixes for MySQL and PostgreSQL.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour` Table : language column, note column, index state, index language.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour-steps`  Table : language column, note column, index state, index language, modified column `setp-no` to `step_no`, modified column `interactivetour` to `interactive_type`.
- [x] Addition of an admin module in replacement to the toolbars.
- [x] Calls via Ajax to avoid refreshes if the module is on the same page of a tour.
- [x] Changed `Step Name` to `Step`.
- [x] Changed `Interactive Tour` to `Interactive Step` in Steps.
- [x] Added Step Type column in Steps.
- [x] Fixed PHP 8.1 depreciation error.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Tours.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Steps.
- [x] Admin module database changes.
- [x] Tours in the database have been replaced with language keys for proper translations.
- [x] Empty state for steps view when no step has ever been created for a tour.
- [x] Added getEmptyStateQuery to return the steps of a tour.
- [x] Added columns access, featured, and locked.
- [x] Replaced 'click' with `select` in steps.
- [x] Fix EOF.
- [x] Fix filter forms (default sort, dropdown elements ordering).
- [x] Component name lowercase in the manifest.
- [x] Cleanup component provider.
- [x] Converted module `mod_guidedtour`s to services.
- [x] Remove loading of language files.
- [x] Fixed the `Take a Tour` button visible before logging in.
- [x] Added focus on targeted elements.
- [x] Changes to tours to render targeted elements.
- [x] Accessible (in some cases, targeted elements were not tab-able).
- [x] Tours can't show if no user is logged in.
- [x] Selection of tours per language, access and component authorization.
- [x] Fixed Step Permission.
- [x] Reordering of the steps according to `tour_id`.
- [x] Created Empty State for Tours.
- [x] Languages inherited from parent tour in steps.
- [x] Added access column in tours.
- [x] Added note section for tours and steps.
- [x] Core tours and their steps, in a multilingual environment, can not be saved or else language keys are overridden.
- [x] Formatted database queries.
- [x] Created functionality for tour duplication along with its steps.
- [x] The step count only considers the number of published steps.
- [x] Fixed the width of the step table.
- [x] Unsets the `tour_id `from the active filters so that the search tools open in a closed state.
- [x] Allowed the creation of a custom admin menu for the guided tours component.
- [x] Fixed Typos in order url task attribute.
- [x] Fixed saving to asset table.
- [x] Removed the step_no column.
- [x] Ordering in the script, done through ordering property and not id.
- [x] Fixes for saving tours and steps.
- [x] Added a Full list of buttons to remove in editor `hide`.
- [x] Fixed `bleeding` over popup. 
- [x] Added empty state.


#### Added default Tours that need to be created, to be packaged with Joomla Basic tours required for this project.

- [x] Guided Tour Introduction
- [x] Content > Articles
- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- Created base structure for Guided Tour.
- This feature is a click-through path which the user can follow to fulfill certain tasks and it will increase the convenience for the users.
- With this feature users don't need to read the bulky documentation.

### Testing Instructions

- Apply the patch.
- Go to System and click on Plugin under the Manage section.
- Enable the `Guided Tours` plugin.
- Click on `Guided Tours` under the Manage section.
- Now, as the Plugin is enabled you can see the `Take the Tour` button.
- Click on the `Take the Tour` button and select the Guided Tour which you want.

![Guided Tour](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316197-39c8e30a-3928-4be0-a5dc-6f9d0b321475.PNG)

![Guided Tour 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316213-ec0d658a-8de3-404f-824c-12f9c1542b63.PNG)

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

- Guided Tour functionality was not present.

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

- Included Guided Tour functionality.

### Summary

- [x] Created Base Structure for Guided Tour.
- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Created Relative URL for Steps and Tours.
- [x] Removed the `https://` from the URL to make the tour work.
- [x] Solved URL problem for Tours Page. 
- [x] Made `Back Button` Functional for Multi-Page.
- [x] Added String Value for Archived Tours.
- [x] Added Table Structure and data for Guided Tours and Steps for Postgresql.
- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Changes done in PR: https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/10.
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.
- [x] Added form fields in the tour step for an interactive tour.
- [x] Changed value for interactive step field in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Add a new dropdown field that would be visible after selecting Interactive tour which has two options - Button and Text Field.
- [x] Solved the major problem for the interactive step and made `+New Button` Working.
- [x]  If the user selects the `Button` field then the user will be able to click the `+New button` in spite of clicking on the `Next Button` in the pop-up.
- [x] On selecting the `Button` field the Next Button won't be visible.
- [x] If the user selects the `Text field` then it will disable the Next Button until someone enters any value in the field.
- [x] Added EventListner `Click` on the target of the step for the Button field in Interactive Tour.
- [x] Added EventListner `input` on the target of the step for Form Field.
- [x] Done changes for default tours in `extensions.sql` for changing the value according to Interactive tour.
- [x] Code formatting.
- [x] Added one more field in the `Interactive step` for default values.
- [x] Added logic in javascript for incorporating changes for adding one more field in the `Interactive step`.
- [x] Made changes in default tours in `extensions.sql`  to make it compatible with interactive tours.
- [x] Identified and solved the problem and made two consecutive mandatory fields `Next Button` enable/disable in the `interactive step` work.
- [x] Tested the changes done for all the default tours to ensure all the tours are working with interaction.
- [x] Did the changes in Default tours and made improvements in interactive tours.
- [x] Done Update SQL scripts fixes for MySQL and PostgreSQL.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour` Table : language column, note column, index state, index language.
- [x] Added in `guidedtour-steps`  Table : language column, note column, index state, index language, modified column `setp-no` to `step_no`, modified column `interactivetour` to `interactive_type`.
- [x] Addition of an admin module in replacement to the toolbars.
- [x] Calls via Ajax to avoid refreshes if the module is on the same page of a tour.
- [x] Changed `Step Name` to `Step`.
- [x] Changed `Interactive Tour` to `Interactive Step` in Steps.
- [x] Added Step Type column in Steps.
- [x] Fixed PHP 8.1 depreciation error.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Tours.
- [x] Added permissions to own tab in Steps.
- [x] Admin module database changes.
- [x] Tours in the database have been replaced with language keys for proper translations.
- [x] Empty state for steps view when no step has ever been created for a tour.
- [x] Added getEmptyStateQuery to return the steps of a tour.
- [x] Added columns access, featured, and locked.
- [x] Replaced 'click' with `select` in steps.
- [x] Fix EOF.
- [x] Fix filter forms (default sort, dropdown elements ordering).
- [x] Component name lowercase in the manifest.
- [x] Cleanup component provider.
- [x] Converted module `mod_guidedtour`s to services.
- [x] Remove loading of language files.
- [x] Fixed the `Take a Tour` button visible before logging in.
- [x] Added focus on targeted elements.
- [x] Changes to tours to render targeted elements.
- [x] Accessible (in some cases, targeted elements were not tab-able).
- [x] Tours can't show if no user is logged in.
- [x] Selection of tours per language, access and component authorization.
- [x] Fixed Step Permission.
- [x] Reordering of the steps according to `tour_id`.
- [x] Created Empty State for Tours.
- [x] Languages inherited from parent tour in steps.
- [x] Added access column in tours.
- [x] Added note section for tours and steps.
- [x] Core tours and their steps, in a multilingual environment, can not be saved or else language keys are overridden.
- [x] Formatted database queries.
- [x] Created functionality for tour duplication along with its steps.
- [x] The step count only considers the number of published steps.
- [x] Fixed the width of the step table.
- [x] Unsets the `tour_id `from the active filters so that the search tools open in a closed state.
- [x] Allowed the creation of a custom admin menu for the guided tours component.
- [x] Fixed Typos in order url task attribute.
- [x] Fixed saving to asset table.
- [x] Removed the step_no column.
- [x] Ordering in the script, done through ordering property and not id.
- [x] Fixes for saving tours and steps.
- [x] Added a Full list of buttons to remove in editor `hide`.
- [x] Fixed `bleeding` over popup. 
- [x] Added empty state.

pr_body:
Pull Request for Issue #7.

### Summary of Changes
#### Added default Tours that need to be created, to be packaged with Joomla Basic tours required for this project.

- [x] Guided Tour Introduction
- [x] Content > Articles
- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

#### Other Changes
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.
- [x] Done changes in Extensions.sql for adding `type` and `validation` field.
- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.
- [x] Removed hidden field label and added string value for step title label.
- [x] Done PHPCS fixes.
- [x] Removed hidden field string value.
- [x] Code Cleanup for guidedtours.xml.
- [x] Added fields for the interactive tour in default-tours.
- [x] Got passed all the build tests.

### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.

- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.

pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- Created base structure for Guided Tour.
- This feature is a click-through path which the user can follow to fulfill certain tasks and it will increase the convenience for the users.
- With this feature users don't need to read the bulky documentation.

### Testing Instructions

- Apply the patch.
- Go to System and click on Plugin under the Manage section.
- Enable the `Guided Tours` plugin.
- Click on `Guided Tours` under the Manage section.
- Now, as the Plugin is enabled you can see the `Take the Tour` button.
- Click on the `Take the Tour` button and select the Guided Tour which you want.

![Guided Tour](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316197-39c8e30a-3928-4be0-a5dc-6f9d0b321475.PNG)

![Guided Tour 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60094678/174316213-ec0d658a-8de3-404f-824c-12f9c1542b63.PNG)

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

- Guided Tour functionality was not present.

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

- Included Guided Tour functionality.

### Summary

- [x] Created Base Structure for Guided Tour.
- [x] Fixed save2new button in Step Page.
- [x] Made saveAsCopy working in Step section.
- [x] Created a working single-page tour.
- [x] Made steps URL re-direction working.
- [x] Solved the URL problem of the Guided Tour feature.
- [x] Solved the `StepID` problem.
- [x] Optimized and removed redundant code of the script file.
- [x] Modularized and re-written the entire script file.
- [x] Made the Overlay Option permanently true for every tour.
- [x] Made tour work from any page the user starts it.
- [x] Minor changes in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Created Relative URL for Steps and Tours.
- [x] Removed the `https://` from the URL to make the tour work.
- [x] Solved URL problem for Tours Page. 
- [x] Made `Back Button` Functional for Multi-Page.
- [x] Added String Value for Archived Tours.
- [x] Added Table Structure and data for Guided Tours and Steps for Postgresql.
- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.

pr_body:
Pull Request for PR #6 .

### Summary of Changes

This Pull Request (PR) fixes errors in the installation and update SQL scripts and one error in the tours model and adapts the update SQL scripts to the enhancements made with PR https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/37156 for the 4.2 version for more fault tolerant update SQL scripts.

The changes have been made with several commits in a comprehensive way so you can understand why a change has been made.

Simply go to the list of commits of this PR. You can expand the descriptions with details or links to details by using the "..." right beside the title of each commit.

By clicking on the title (or better right click and chose open in a new tab) you can then see the changes made with this commit.

### Testing Instructions

Check that a new installation and after that login to backend work without SQL errors on all kinds or supported databases (MySQL or MariaDB and PostgreSQL).

Check that updating any 3.10 or 4.x version to a package build with this PR and after that login to backend work without SQL errors on all kinds or supported databases (MySQL or MariaDB and PostgreSQL).

### Actual result BEFORE applying this Pull Request

New installations and updates fail for sure with PostgreSQL.

Hard-coded user IDs used for created by and modified by users for the new data on new installations and updates.

On PostgreSQL you get an SQL error due to hardcoded MySQL names quotes being used in an SQL query in the guided tours model.

MySQL data types were used in SQL scripts for PostgreSQL.

Wrong data types (strings instead of numbers or datetimes/timestamps) used for values in insert statements.

....

### Expected result AFTER applying this Pull Request

No such errors anymore.

### Documentation Changes Required

None.

pr_body:
Pull Request for Issue #7.

### Summary of Changes
#### Added default Tours that need to be created, to be packaged with Joomla Basic tours required for this project.

- [x] Guided Tour Introduction
- [x] Content > Articles
- [x] Content > Categories
- [x]  Menus
- [x]  Banners
- [x] Tags
- [x] Contacts
- [x] News Feeds
- [x] Smart Search
- [x] Users

#### Other Changes
- [x] Added the default-tours.
- [x] Renamed the Next button to the Start button.  
- [x] Sync up changes with the cleanup branch.
- [x] Used correct Values for Created, Modified and Checked out columns in `extensions.sql`.
- [x] Updated `extensions.sql` file.
- [x] Code cleanup for `default-tours` branch.
- [x] Added form fields for interactive and click-through tours.
- [x] Changed default values in step.xml.
- [x] Merged branch `cleanup` with `infra-guided-tour` and rebased the `default-tours` branch from `infra-guided-tour`.
- [x] Added functionality for the next step and redirect.
- [x] Added string value for URL.

- [x] Syncup the branch with `4.3-dev`.

pr_title: Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL and Code Cleanup
pr_body:
### Summary of Changes

- [x] Optimized Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Converted 2 Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL into one.
- [x] Removed Label from Hidden Field.
- [x] Code Cleanup
- [x] Update String Value for Relative URL.
- [x] Increase the file version to 4.3 for Update SQL Scripts for Postgresql and MySQL.
- [x] Follow Coding Standards.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Errors from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the PHPCS Warnings from logs for getting the build tests passed.
- [x] Resolved the comments for code cleanup.
- [x] Used Standard Headings for the Views and removed the tours id from the title in the steps view.
- [x] Resolved the code review of PR #1.
- [x] Removed Overlay Option permanently and made it permanently true for every tour.
